abstract: Dow Jones industrial average gains 37.16 points, or 0.32 percent, to 11,541.78; Standard & Poor's 500-stock index gains 5.51 points, or 0.46 percent, to 1,215.39; Nasdaq composite index slips 5.42 points, or 0.21 percent, to 2,598.62.
snippet: Investors were looking for direction from corporate earnings as European leaders sought to reassure markets that a solution to the debt crisis would come soon.
lead_paragraph: Investors were looking for direction from corporate earnings as European leaders sought to reassure markets that a solution to the debt crisis would come soon.

headline.main: Wall Street Ends Mixed on Uncertainty Over Europe
headline.print_headline: Wall Street Ends Mixed on Uncertainty Over Europe
